      "html": "<h1>The Javascript Konami Event Listener</h1>\n<h3>Adds the event listener that always should have been standard in all browsers.</h3>\n<h2>Use</h2>\n<p>You can use the konami event listener like you would any event listener. At the moment, it only applies to the document.</p>\n<pre><span class=\"hljs-built_in\">document</span>.onKonami = <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\">function</span>(<span class=\"hljs-params\"></span>)</span>{\n    alert(<span class=\"hljs-string\">&quot;KONAMI!&quot;</span>);\n}</pre><p>If you are unaware what the konami code is it is a cheat code that is activated by hitting the following keys in order:</p>\n<p><strong>Up Up Down Down Left Right Left Right B A</strong></p>\n"
